\end_inset

its just wave equations in curved spacetime, just like in textbooks.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 But perhaps this is too much to hope for.
 Maybe the textbooks are right.
 I'm starting to suspect the textbooks are right.
 Erm.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The next issue is QFT.
 The Huygens sum can be imagined as tree-level Feynmann diagrams.
 What about loops? The textbook answer here is that there are textbooks
 on this, too.
 At least, for mild curvatures, which are not too large, one can write down
