\begin_layout Subsection*
Relation to Schwarschild coords
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

 be the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

time at infinity
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, i.e.
 the Schwarschild time.
 The relation between 
\begin_inset Formula $T$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

 is the Gullstrand–Painlevé chart is
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
t\left(T,r\right) & =T+\int\frac{\sqrt{2m/r}}{1-2m/r}dr\\
 & =T-2m\left(2y-\log\left(\frac{y-1}{y+1}\right)\right)
\end{align*}

\end_inset

with 
\begin_inset Formula $y=\sqrt{r/2m}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $0<r<\infty$
\end_inset

.
 The log hits the branch point at 
\begin_inset Formula $r=2m$
\end_inset

; this is the coordinate singularity in the Schwarschild chart.
\end_layout

